This paper deals with voting rules and strategic voting, which are topics commonly studied in the field of computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of computing strategic votes, which is a topic relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of scoring rules and tournament graphs also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
